How to Run this Project Steps-by-Steps: 

We are using:

AWS Lambda

Amazon S3

Amazon DynamoDB

Amazon SNS

Amazon EventBridge

Amazon Athena


COMPLETE STEP-BY-STEP: Run the Project
STEP 1: Create S3 Bucket

Open AWS Console

Go to S3

Click Create bucket

Name:

real-time-stock-analytics-yourname

Create bucket

Inside bucket → Create folder:

raw-data/

STEP 2: Create DynamoDB Table

Go to DynamoDB

Click Create table

Table name:

stock_prices

Partition key:

symbol (String)

Create table

STEP 3: Create SNS Topic (For Alerts)

Go to SNS

Create Topic → Standard

Name:

stock-alert-topic

Create subscription:

Protocol: Email

Enter your email

Confirm email subscription

Copy the Topic ARN (you’ll need it).


STEP 4: Get API Key

Go to Finnhub.io
Create free account
Copy API key

STEP 5: Create IAM Role for Lambda

Go to IAM → Roles → Create Role

Trusted entity:

Lambda

Attach policies:

AmazonS3FullAccess

AmazonDynamoDBFullAccess

AmazonSNSFullAccess

AWSLambdaBasicExecutionRole

Name:

lambda-stock-role

STEP 6: Create Lambda Function

Go to Lambda

Create function

Name:

stock-processor

Runtime: Python 3.10

Choose role: lambda-stock-role

🔧 Configure Environment Variables (Important)

In Lambda → Configuration → Environment variables:

Add:

API_KEY = your_actual_api_key
BUCKET_NAME = real-time-stock-analytics-yourname
TABLE_NAME = stock_prices
SNS_TOPIC_ARN = your_sns_topic_arn

STEP 7: Upload Lambda Code

Open lambda_function.py

Paste your code

Click Deploy

STEP 8: Test Lambda Manually (Before Automation)

Click Test

Create test event (default JSON is fine)

Click Test

If successful:

StatusCode = 200

No errors

STEP 9: Check If Data is Stored

After testing:

✔ Check S3

Open bucket → raw-data
You should see JSON files.

✔ Check DynamoDB

Open table → Explore items
You should see stock price row.

✔ Check Email

If price > threshold → SNS email sent.


STEP 10: Automate Using EventBridge

Open EventBridge

Create Rule

Choose Schedule

Rate-based expression:

rate(5 minutes)

Target:

Lambda → stock-processor

Create rule

Now it runs automatically every 5 minutes.


STEP 11: Configure Athena

Open Athena

Set query result location (choose your S3 bucket)

Run:

CREATE DATABASE stockdb;

Then:

CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE stock_data (
  c double,
  h double,
  l double,
  o double,
  pc double
)
ROW FORMAT SERDE 'org.openx.data.jsonserde.JsonSerDe'
LOCATION 's3://real-time-stock-analytics-yourname/raw-data/';

Now test:

SELECT * FROM stock_data;

If rows appear → Project is running successfully 🎉

🎯 How To Confirm Project Is Fully Running

✔ Lambda logs updating every 5 min
✔ S3 files increasing
✔ DynamoDB updating
✔ Athena query returning results
✔ SNS alert working

If all 5 working → System is LIVE 🚀
